    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CATERPILLAR 3406B -1991 - DESCRIPTION - Electronic Governor
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Electronic Governor</title>
        <para>PEEC engines have an electronically controlled, hydraulically actuated governor. A double acting hydraulic
            servo provides muscle for moving the fuel rack. The engine RPM sensor is inside the governor as is a fuel
            shutoff solenoid that is controlled by PEEC.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
